cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This is the most likely category as the paper is focused on the cryptanalysis of a chaotic image encryption algorithm and evaluating its security properties. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - Information entropy is a key concept in the algorithm and the paper evaluates the validity of the used quantifiable security metrics, which could fall under the scope of information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper mentions the use of a digital chaotic system in the encryption algorithm, which could fall under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper is focused on the security of an image encryption algorithm, which falls under the scope of multimedia security. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper is focused on the security of an image encryption algorithm, which could fall under the scope of computer vision and pattern recognition.
